<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="specific-adj">specific <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /spə'sɪfɪk/    美 /spə'sɪfɪk/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>明确的；详细的</strong></h4>
<p>detailed and exact (precise)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a specific goal / answer
明确的目标/答案</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In this article, you need to back up general statements with specific examples.
在这篇文章中，你得用具体的实例来支撑自己的概括性陈述。</p><footer>2016 浙江</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-particular">2.★ <strong>[只用于名词前] 特有的；特定的(particular)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s a way of living <strong>specific to</strong> America.
这是美国特有的生活方式。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We discourage you from smoking except in specific areas.
除特定区域外，我们禁止吸烟。</p><footer>外研⑧ – 1</footer></div></div>